Preset card art ingestion folder (09.1-CONTEXT.md D-09).

Convention: drop one folder per preset here, named by preset_id, containing:

  assets/preset-art/<preset_id>/poster.jpg   (required if ffmpeg is not installed)
  assets/preset-art/<preset_id>/loop.mp4     (required)

Example:

  assets/preset-art/motion-transfer/poster.jpg
  assets/preset-art/motion-transfer/loop.mp4
  assets/preset-art/try-on/poster.jpg
  assets/preset-art/try-on/loop.mp4

Then run:

  npm run upload:preset-art

This scans every folder here, uploads to version-suffixed R2 keys
(presets/<preset_id>/poster-v<N>.jpg, loop-v<N>.mp4), and prints the
resulting stable URLs to paste into src/config/presets.ts.

If ffmpeg is installed locally, loop.mp4 is transcoded to the card-art
contract (~480x640, H.264 baseline, no audio) and poster.jpg is
auto-extracted from the first frame if you didn't supply one. If ffmpeg
is not installed, files are uploaded as-is — supply pre-encoded files.

Files in this folder are local-only working files, not committed to git
(see .gitignore) other than this placeholder.
